OL,3,CMan 'forced to live in car' after
OL,4,Cspending 80% of wage to rent a room
OL,6,FPaul hopes the island's government can
OL,7,Fincrease the amount of help it gives
OL,8,Fto those on low incomes but he is not
OL,9,Foptimistic about the future due to the
OL,10,Flack of affordable social housing and
OL,11,Fthe high cost of living.
OL,13,FHe adds: "To be honest I feel sorry
OL,14,Ffor the kids growing up over here with
OL,15,Fthe amount and cost of property and
OL,16,Frentals.
OL,18,F"A child going into a shop on a
OL,19,Fminimum wage is going to struggle
OL,20,Fbefore they even become an adult."
