OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F381A1725378846
OL,3,CMan 'forced to live in car' after
OL,4,Cspending 80% of wage to rent a room
OL,6,F"The situation is pretty stark. The
OL,7,Ffact is, there isn't enough social
OL,8,Fhousing, there isn't enough affordable
OL,9,Fhousing for people to move into. The
OL,10,Fwaiting list is very long, you can be
OL,11,Fwaiting for years before you're
OL,12,Foffered social housing so that needs
OL,13,Fto change.
OL,15,F"Private rental costs are phenomenally
OL,16,Fhigh almost compared to any other
OL,17,Fjurisdiction on the planet.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/10
